    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All thirteen credibility factors were assessed or flagged. Seven factors were assessed with achieved levels below required levels; six factors were flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite these gaps, the overall hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold across all five operating points and the Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds are acceptable. The assessment team accepted the package with the understanding that re-validation against the 2026 model revision will be conducted prior to regulatory submission. The stale 2018 validation dataset was not identified as a blocking issue.",
